
     <only-one> 

       An only-one archive has sub directories:  bin, src, store, and tax.  It
       has a file named 'version'.

     <only-one>/bin/

       has programs such as 'insert'

     <only-one>/src/

       has the source code for the bin programs.

     <only-one>/store/

       has the node files. Node files have numbers for names.  Each is a unique file.


     <only-one>/tax/
        has the taxonomy

        Each 'sources' file holds the list of pathnames found for each node. Each pathname
        also has an mtime.  The name 'sources' is followed by a semicolon and a version
        number.  sources;0 is the most up to date.

     <only-one>/version 

